> Craving the ultimate throwback of the humble sloppy joe—minus the meat? Look no
> further. This version stars ground plant-based protein, and is worlds tastier
> than the ones the lunch lady slung: Think pickled onion, a smoky BBQ sauce,
> and a side of hearty potato wedges.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a
#baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the Southwest Spice later.)

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Cut broccoli florets into bite-size pieces if necessary. Swap in broccoli for
> potatoes. (Save potatoes for another use.)

While potatoes roast, halve, peel, and very thinly slice ¼ of the
@Red Onion{1}; finely chop remaining. Quarter @Lemon{1}. Halve
@Brioche Buns{2}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the
lemon, @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of salt. Microwave until onion is softened,
~{1%minute}. Set aside.

In a second #small bowl{}, combine @BBQ Sauce{4%tbsp}, @Ketchup{2%tbsp},
@Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1}, half the @Cornstarch{1%tbsp}, remaining
@Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp}, and @water{1%tbsp}.

In a third small bowl, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and a squeeze of lemon
juice. Season with salt.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chopped onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @Ground Plant-Based Protein{6%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Using a
#spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned on
bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned all over and
warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Add @water{2%tbsp} to pan with plant-based protein, then stir in BBQ sauce
mixture. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. (TIP: If
sauce seems too thick, add another splash of water.) Taste and season with salt
and pepper. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, toast buns until golden brown.

Divide buns between #plates{}; spread cut sides of bottom buns with lemon mayo.
Fill buns with messy jane filling and as much pickled onion (draining first) as
you like. Serve with @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} on the side and any remaining
lemon mayo for dipping.